>NAME

getsid - get session ID of a process

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <sys/types.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	
	pid_t getsid(pid_t 'pid');

>DESCRIPTION

This function returns the session ID of the process with the process ID 'pid'. If 'pid' is 0, it returns the session ID of the calling process.

>RETURN VALUE

On sucess, returns a positive integer specifying the session ID of the specified process. On error, '-1' is returned, and [errno.6] is set appropriately.

>ERRORS

On error, this function returns '-1' and sets [errno.6] to one of the following:

\* *ESRCH* - 'pid' is not zero and a process with the given 'pid' does not exist.

